            "How can I retrieve the DDL statement for a BigQuery table to recreate its schema and data layout?\n",
            "To retrieve the **DDL (Data Definition Language)** statement for a BigQuery table and recreate its schema and data layout, you can use the **`INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES`** view. This method works for both **native (managed) tables** and **external tables**.\n",
            "\n",
            "---\n",
            "\n",
            "### **Steps to Retrieve DDL for a BigQuery Table**\n",
            "\n",
            "#### **1. For Native (Managed) Tables**\n",
            "Run the following query, replacing `your_dataset` and `your_table_name` with your dataset and table names:\n",
            "\n",
            "```sql\n",
            "SELECT table_name, ddl\n",
            "FROM `your_dataset`.INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES\n",
            "WHERE table_name = 'your_table_name';\n",
            "```\n",
            "\n",
            "**Example:**\n",
            "```sql\n",
            "SELECT table_name, ddl\n",
            "FROM `zoomcamp.INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES`\n",
            "WHERE table_name = 'yellow_tripdata_parquet';\n",
            "```\n",
            "\n",
            "This will return the `CREATE TABLE` statement required to recreate the table, including all columns, data types, and constraints.\n",
            "\n",
            "---\n",
            "\n",
            "#### **2. For External Tables**\n",
            "The process is the same, but the DDL will include the `OPTIONS` clause specifying the external data source (e.g., format and file URIs).\n",
            "\n",
            "**Example:**\n",
            "```sql\n",
            "SELECT table_name, ddl\n",
            "FROM `zoomcamp.INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES`\n",
            "WHERE table_name = 'yellow_tripdata_parquet_ext';\n",
            "```\n",
            "\n",
            "The result will look like:\n",
            "```sql\n",
            "CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE `zoomcamp-ingenieria-datos.zoomcamp.yellow_tripdata_parquet_ext`\n",
            "OPTIONS(\n",
            "    format=\"PARQUET\",\n",
            "    uris=[\"gs://newyork-taxi/yellow_tripdata_*.parquet\"]\n",
            ");\n",
            "```\n",
            "\n",
            "---\n",
            "\n",
            "### **Key Notes**\n",
            "- This method works for both **native** and **external** tables.\n",
            "- The `ddl` column in the `INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES` view contains the full `CREATE TABLE` or `CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE` statement.\n",
            "- For more details, refer to the [BigQuery `INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES` documentation](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/information-schema-tables).\n",
            "\n",
