            "I'm getting an error with my `docker-compose.yaml` file: 'service pgdatabase refers to undefined volume dtc_postgres_volume_local'. How can I fix this?\n",
            "The error `'service pgdatabase refers to undefined volume dtc_postgres_volume_local'` occurs because the `docker-compose.yaml` file references a volume (`dtc_postgres_volume_local`) that hasn't been defined in the `volumes` section of the file.\n",
            "\n",
            "### Solution:\n",
            "Add the volume definition to your `docker-compose.yaml` file under the `volumes` section. Here's how you can fix it:\n",
            "\n",
            "```yaml\n",
            "volumes:\n",
            "  dtc_postgres_volume_local:\n",
            "```\n",
            "\n",
            "### Example:\n",
            "Your `docker-compose.yaml` should include something like this:\n",
            "\n",
            "```yaml\n",
            "services:\n",
            "  pgdatabase:\n",
            "    image: postgres:13\n",
            "    volumes:\n",
            "      - dtc_postgres_volume_local:/var/lib/postgresql/data\n",
            "    # ... other configurations ...\n",
            "\n",
            "volumes:\n",
            "  dtc_postgres_volume_local:\n",
            "```\n",
            "\n",
            "### Steps:\n",
            "1. Open your `docker-compose.yaml` file.\n",
            "2. Add the `volumes` section at the root level (same level as `services`).\n",
            "3. Define the volume `dtc_postgres_volume_local` as shown above.\n",
            "4. Save the file and run `docker compose up` again.\n",
